gomodel:SYNGO_2623  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: From Results section:\n\n\"To determine whether mammalian Class C Vps proteins are involved in Ca2+-dependent exocytosis, hGH expression vector (pXGH5) was co-transfected with\nmammalian Class C Vps expression vectors.\" (...) \"The hGH-release, represented by the ratio of the hGH concentration in supernatant/lysate, was significantly\npotentiated when the mammalian Class C Vps molecules were co-transfected (Fig. 4). The potentiation of hGH-release was completely blocked in the presence of nifedipine, a L-type Ca2+-channel blocker.\"\n\n\"The potentiation of hGH-release was abolished by replacing full-length-hVps11, -hVps18, with DRING-hVps11, -hVps18, respectively (see Supplemental Fig. 3)\"\n\n22/2/2018 Pim\nFig. 5. \"Effects of hVps18-overexpression on synaptic responses in cultured hippocampal neurons\"\n\nAbstract: \"These results indicate that mammalian Class C Vps proteins are involved in the regulation of membrane docking and fusion through an interaction with neuronal specific SNARE molecules, nSec-1/Munc18-a and syntaxin 1A.\". Experimental description: From M&M section:\nThe HA-tagged mammalian Class C Vps constructs were described previously [10,14]. *Paper [10] listed below in \"Additional literature\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6893-6177" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5265-6306" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-19" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2623" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_9606" .

